d — file type. The first character tells you what it is. d = directory (folder). A - here would mean a regular file. l would mean a symbolic link.
rwxr-xr-x — permissions. This 9-character block is split into 3 groups of 3:

rwx → the owner (root) can read, write, and enter
r-x → the group (adm) can read and enter, but NOT write
r-x → everyone else can also read and enter, but NOT write
